      <div class="msgContentFrame">Today it happened for the first time since closed beta: <br />For more than half an hour, I didn't find anyone to repair my equipment in Ul'dah in front of <br />the repair NPC. There were just 5(!) active crafters around, and none of them was able to do <br />the specific job I required (leather and goldsmithing). <br /> <br />Something is rotten when you have to wait for 30 minutes in vain just to get your gear repaired. <br /> <br />(P.S.: Repair costs at the NPC are a no-go, and he'll not repair accessories. And no, being a <br />casual I don't have the time to level 5 crafting jobs either).</div>
